CRITICAL DISCLAIMER - PACER FEES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:

PACER charges fees for document access. Users of this software are SOLELY 
responsible for:
- Understanding PACER's fee structure ($0.10 per page, capped at $30/quarter)
- Obtaining and verifying fee exemptions if applicable
- Ensuring fee exemptions are properly applied to their account
- Monitoring their PACER account for charges
- All costs incurred through use of this software

This software was developed for academic research on litigation in US federal 
courts. It has been tested primarily on US Courts of Appeals and may behave 
differently on other court types (District Courts, Bankruptcy Courts, etc.).

THE AUTHOR IS NOT RESPONSIBLE FOR:
- Any fees or charges incurred through use of this software
- Verification of fee exemption status
- Changes to PACER's fee structure or policies
- Misuse or violations of PACER Terms of Service
- Use of this software without proper fee exemption verification

This software is intended ONLY for legitimate academic research purposes.
Bulk downloading for commercial purposes, resale, or non-research uses is
prohibited and violates PACER's Acceptable Use Policy.

Users MUST:
- Read and comply with PACER Terms of Service and Acceptable Use Policy
- Understand their account's fee exemption status BEFORE using this software
- Verify fee exemption is active and applies to their intended use
- Monitor their PACER account for any unexpected charges
- Respect rate limits and court system resources
- Use only for legitimate research purposes

For fee exemption information, see:
https://pacer.uscourts.gov/my-account-billing/billing/fee-exemption-request-researchers
